# Projects Manifest

*Last updated: YYYY-MM-DD*

Single source of truth for every project reachable from this meta-workspace, plus the recipe to recreate the topology on a fresh machine.

> Copy to `PROJECTS.md` (drop the `.template` suffix) and edit as you add projects.

> **The pattern:** This repo (`<<EDIT: your meta-workspace name>>`) is the **meta-workspace**. Open it in Cursor / AntiGravity as the workspace root — that loads the registered MCPs and gives the agent direct filesystem access to every linked project. Working from inside an individual client repo as the workspace root works for git operations and quick edits but loses MCP access (Cursor only loads MCPs from the workspace root's `.cursor/mcp.json`, not from symlinked subdirs).

