## Setup on a fresh machine

```bash
cd ~/Documents/GitHub

# Clone the meta-workspace
git clone <<EDIT: meta-workspace URL>>

# Clone client engagements (one per active client)
git clone <<EDIT: client URL>> <<EDIT: client folder>>

# Wire the meta-workspace (one-line shell, ask your AI if you want)
cd <<EDIT: meta-workspace folder>>
ln -s ../.claude/skills .cursor/skills      # so IDE skill discovery sees them
mkdir -p clients personal vault/People vault/Companies
ln -s "../../<<EDIT: client folder>>" clients/<<EDIT: client slug>>

# Shell env (add to ~/.zshrc or equivalent)
export VAULT_DATA_ROOT="$HOME/Documents/GitHub/<<EDIT: meta-workspace folder>>/vault"
# Plus any adapter / API keys you use, e.g.
# export FATHOM_API_KEY=...

# Cursor / AntiGravity: open the meta-workspace folder as the workspace root.
```

Optional: if using Claude Desktop, also configure `~/.config/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json` (or macOS equivalent) to register the same MCPs with the same env block.

